                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180617-176-off980 t18180617-176-crimeloc983"></join>. On the 23d of May, the prisoner came to the shop, and offered a duplicate for sale. My husband told him to stop while he fetched the article; he pulled the handkerchief down, and ran out with it; I ran out, but he got out of my sight. In about half an hour he returned and asked for the money for the duplicate. I gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I said I was going up the street and would return.</p>
